OPERATOR-ONLY PATCH — issue #1221 SharePoint federated-search cutover, step C.

WHY THIS IS NOT IN THE REPO
===========================
The one genuinely unavoidable upstream change is making ahg-federation's
FederatedSearchService dispatcher EXTENSIBLE so the SharePoint connector class is
contributed by ahg-sharepoint (via config('federation.connectors')) instead of
being hard-coded in ahg-federation source.

That file is BOTH:
  * locked      — packages/ahg-federation/src/Services/FederatedSearchService.php
                  is in .locked-paths (the F3 SharePoint federated-search lock,
                  lines 188-194), so it cannot be committed/released without an
                  explicit operator ./bin/unlock; and
  * no-push     — per the SharePoint NO-PUSH policy
                  (memory/f3_federation_sharepoint_local.md), the F3 federation
                  files NEVER commit and NEVER release. Their canonical source of
                  truth is /opt/ahg-sp-integration/F3/, which is operator-managed.

Therefore this agent CANNOT and MUST NOT edit that file in the repo. The change
below is applied by the OPERATOR to the canonical source, NOT pushed from here:

  Canonical target (operator applies here):
    /opt/ahg-sp-integration/F3/heratio/src/Services/FederatedSearchService.php

  When the operator later PROMOTES F3 into the live tree (MIGRATION.md step B),
  the promoted FederatedSearchService.php already carries this change, and the
  SharePoint FQCN never appears in ahg-federation source — ahg-sharepoint's
  service provider supplies it through config('federation.connectors').

WHAT THE PATCH DOES
===================
Replaces the hard-coded match() in connectorClassFor() with a registry-first
lookup:
  1. consult config('federation.connectors')[$peerType] — this is the map that
     ahg-sharepoint publishes in AhgSharePointServiceProvider::register():
         'sharepoint_graph_search' =>
             \AhgSharePoint\Federation\SharePointGraphConnector::class
     so any package can contribute a connector for its own peer_type.
  2. fall back to the GENERAL connectors that legitimately stay in
     ahg-federation (atom_local). The 'sharepoint_graph_search' literal is
     REMOVED from ahg-federation source.

The contract-decision (MIGRATION.md, "Contract placement decision") collapses to
OPTION 1 at the same time: the relocated ahg-sharepoint connector implements
\AhgFederation\Connectors\PeerConnector and returns
\AhgFederation\Connectors\PeerSearchResult (the dispatcher's
connectorResultToLegacy() type-hints the latter). The local
AhgSharePoint\Federation\PeerConnector / PeerSearchResult copies remain in the
package ONLY for its self-contained /sharepoint/federated-search surface, which
does not touch the ahg-federation dispatcher. If the operator prefers option 1
end-to-end, change the two `implements`/return lines in
packages/ahg-sharepoint/src/Federation/SharePointGraphConnector.php to the
\AhgFederation\Connectors\... FQCNs and add "ahg/federation": "@dev" to the
package composer require block. (That edit is inside ahg-sharepoint and is safe
to push; it is deferred here only because ahg-federation's F3 PeerConnector is
not yet in the live tree — promoting it is MIGRATION.md step B, operator-run.)

APPLY (operator, on the canonical /opt source)
==============================================
    cd /opt/ahg-sp-integration/F3/heratio
    git apply /usr/share/nginx/heratio/packages/ahg-sharepoint/cutover.patch   # if /opt is a git tree
    #   – or –
    patch -p1 < /usr/share/nginx/heratio/packages/ahg-sharepoint/cutover.patch

--- a/src/Services/FederatedSearchService.php
+++ b/src/Services/FederatedSearchService.php
@@ -300,13 +300,28 @@

     /** @return class-string|null */
     protected function connectorClassFor(string $peerType): ?string
     {
-        // Hand-coded registry for v0.1.0. Extension point: dispatch via a
-        // container-tagged collection in a later release.
-        return match ($peerType) {
-            'atom_local'              => \AhgFederation\Connectors\AtomElasticsearchConnector::class,
-            'sharepoint_graph_search' => \AhgFederation\Connectors\SharePointGraphConnector::class,
-            default                   => null,
-        };
+        // Registry-first dispatch (issue #1221). Other packages contribute their
+        // own peer_type => connector-class mappings via
+        // config('federation.connectors'); e.g. ahg-sharepoint publishes
+        //   'sharepoint_graph_search' =>
+        //       \AhgSharePoint\Federation\SharePointGraphConnector::class
+        // in its service provider, so the SharePoint FQCN never appears in
+        // ahg-federation source.
+        $registry = (array) config('federation.connectors', []);
+        if (isset($registry[$peerType]) && is_string($registry[$peerType]) && $registry[$peerType] !== '') {
+            return $registry[$peerType];
+        }
+
+        // Built-in GENERAL connectors that stay in ahg-federation.
+        return match ($peerType) {
+            'atom_local' => \AhgFederation\Connectors\AtomElasticsearchConnector::class,
+            default      => null,
+        };
     }
